{{Infobox zoo |zoo_name=Miyajima Public Aquarium ||logo= |logo_width= |logo_caption= |image=宮島水族館 Miyajima Public Aquarium.JPG |image_width=200px |image_caption=entrance of the aquarium |date_opened=1959 |location=10-3 Miyajima, [[Hatsukaichi, Hiroshima|Hatsukaichi]], [[Hiroshima Prefecture]], [[Japan]] |num_animals=13,000 |num_species=350 |members=[[JAZA]] <!-- Image with inadequate rationale removed: [[Image:Japanese Association of Zoos and Aquariums logo.GIF|70px]] --> |website=http://www.sunameri.jp/index.html }}
{{nihongo|'''Miyajima Public Aquarium'''|宮島水族館|Miyajima Suizokukan}} is an aquarium on the island of [[Itsukushima]] in [[Hatsukaichi, Hiroshima]], [[Japan]].
==Overview== There are about 350 variety of aquatic animals include [[finless porpoise]]s, [[sea otter]]s, [[Steller sea lion]]s, [[sea lion]]s and [[penguin]]s. Hours are from January 1 to December 25, 9:00&nbsp;a.m. to 5:00&nbsp;p.m.
==History== {{prose|date=July 2017}} *Opened as a prefectural aquarium in 1959 *Transferred to [[Miyajima, Hiroshima]] as a town aquarium in 1967 *Reconstructed the buildings in 1981 *Began to keep [[sea otter]]s in 1985 *Transferred to [[Hatsukaichi, Hiroshima]] as a city aquarium in 2005 *Planned renewal in 2011
==See also== *[[Japanese Association of Zoos and Aquariums]] *[[Itsukushima]]
==External links== *[http://www.miyajima-aqua.jp/english/index.html Miyajima Public Aquarium] *[http://www.jazga.or.jp/english/index.html Japanese Association of Zoos and Aquariums]{{dead link|date=June 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}
