'''Nanoq Media''' is a company in [[Greenland]], who produces a television station of the same name, as well as the '''Nanoq FM''' radio station. Nanoq Media is also a service provider of broadband internet and digital TV.
The television programming is in the [[Danish language|Danish]] and [[Greenlandic language]]. Nanoq Media began broadcasting on 1 August 2002.
Subscription based digital terrestrial television is currently available in the capital [[Nuuk]], [[Qaqortoq]], [[Ilulissat]] and [[Qasigiannguit]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Nuuk-tv udvider til provinsen|url=http://sermitsiaq.ag/nuuk-tv-udvider-provinsen|accessdate=9 April 2017|publisher=Sermitsiaq AG|date=26 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Nuuk TV udvider igen|url=http://sermitsiaq.ag/nuuk-tv-udvider-igen|accessdate=9 April 2017|publisher=Sermitsiaq AG|date=20 March 2016}}</ref>
Nanoq Media was originally called ''Nuuk TV'' but changed its name to the current name in May 2017 as their services was now available is more cities than just Nuuk.
