mal Jayasinghe || ''Appachchi'' |- | 2015 || Aruna Premaratne || ''Chess''<ref>{{cite web|title=EAP Broadcasting Company wins big at Sumathi Awards 2015|url=http://www.dailymirror.lk/83259/eap-broadcasting-company-wins-big-at-sumathi-awards-2015|publisher=Daily Mirror}}</ref> |- | 2016 || [[Jackson Anthony]] || ''[[Daskon (TV series)|Daskon]]''<ref>{{cite web|title=Sumathi Awards 2016|url=http://www.ceylontoday.lk/article20160701CT20161030.php?id=1769|publisher=Ceylon Today}}</ref> |- | 2017 || Sumith Rathnayake || ''Maddahana''<ref>{{cite web|title=ITN again shines at the Sumathi Awards Festival clinching 16 Awards|url=http://www.itnnews.lk/local-news/itn-again-shines-at-the-sumathi-awards-festival-clinching-16-awards/|publisher=ITN News}}</ref> |- | 2018 || [[Jackson Anthony]] || ''See Raja''<ref>{{cite web|title=Sumathi Awards 2018 award winners|url=http://www.sarasaviya.lk/2018/09/06/?fn=sa1809064|publisher=Sarasaviya}}</ref> |}
