'''Television in Nicaragua''' has a history of more than fifty years. Canal 8, the first terrestrial television channel in the country, started broadcasting on July 15, 1956.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://roirobo.wordpress.com/2009/03/14/la-television-en-nicaragua-genesis-desarrollo-y-actualidad/ |title=La televisión en Nicaragua: génesis, desarrollo y actualidad &#124; Mundo Nòmada |publisher=Roirobo.wordpress.com |date=2009-03-14 |accessdate=2014-02-05}}</ref> Currently there are more than 15 national terrestrial and cable TV channels.
== Television channels == === Terrestrial television channels === * [[Televicentro (Canal 2)|Televicentro Canal 2]] * [[Canal 4 (Nicaragua)|Canal 4]] * [[Canal 6 (Nicaragua)|Canal 6]] * [[Telenica (Canal 8)|Telenica Canal 8]] * [[Canal 9 (Nicaragua)|Canal 9]] * [[Canal 10]] * [[TV Red (Canal 11)|TV RED]] * [[Nicavisión (Canal 12)|Canal 12 Nicavisión]] * [[Viva Nicaragua (Canal 13)|Viva Nicaragua 13]] * [[Canal 15 (Nicaragua)|Canal 15 (100% Noticias)]] (Channel 15 UHF, Channel 63 Claro TV) * [[Enlace Nicaragua (Canal 21)|Enlace Nicaragua]] (Channel 21 UHF, Channel 83 Claro TV) * Extra Plus 37 (Channel 37 UHF, Channel 90 Claro TV)
=== Cable television channels === * [[Vos TV (Canal 14)|Vos TV]] (Channel 14 Claro TV) * Megabox (Channel 76 Claro TV) * [[Atv98]] (Channel 98 Claro TV) * [[CDNN 23]] (Channel 99 Claro TV)
=== Regional television channels === * [[Telenorte Canal 35]] (Channel 35 UHF, Channel 48 ClaroTV [[Estelí]]) * Canal 55 El Lider (Channel 55 UHF, Channel 48 Claro TV [[León and Chinandega, Nicaragua]], Channel 110 Telecable [[León and Chinandega, Nicaragua]]) * Canal 16 Ecovisión, [[Camoapa]]
=== Defunct television channels === * [[Sistema Sandinista de Televisión|SSTV]] (defunct; 1979–1990) * [[Sistema Nacional de Televisión (Nicaragua)|SNTV]] (defunct; 1990–1997) * [[Magic Channel]] * [[ESTV (Canal 11)]] (rebranded as [[Vos TV (Canal 14)]] in 2010)
